The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bengal Twenty20 squad today
                                                   Bengal Twenty20 squad today
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The state senior selection committee, which got its two new members in Malay Banerjee and Mintu Das on Tuesday, will meet on Wednesday to select the team for East Zone T20 Championship. Banerjee and Das replaced Saradindu Mukherjee and Kalyan Chowdhury.         
	Sambaran Banerjee, selection committee chairman, and Devang Gandhi have been retained. It was learnt that Laxmi Ratan Shukla will keep the captaincy.         
	The Bengal squad will have 20 members to start with and the final squad will be pruned to 15 once the team plays two T20 practice matches.         
	Meanwhile, CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya said secretary Biswarup Dey would be attending the Future Tour Programme meeting scheduled to be held in Mumbai on October 9. India play host to Sri Lanka who will be playing three Tests and five ODIs, while South Africa will come calling early next year. The CAB wants the BCCI to allot a match out of those 10 ODIs and six Tests.                                                                                                                       
